I/we need to be able to use "spaceKey=@self" within the livesearch macro. The main reason is so it can be used with live-templates that are included on multiple pages across multiple spaces.

When using viewfile (or now viewxls) to access an excel file  that is password protected...

{viewfile:name=password protected access.xls}

... we see the following error:

{quote}viewfile: com.benryan.conversion.ConvertsionException: error converting spreadsheet{quote}

A copy of the same page/content works fine on our Confluence 2.10.3 production system. (No errors; password protected excel file contents are not rendered by viewfile macro, but the edit button will open this file as expected.)

Users were happy with how this worked on Confluence 2.10.3 production, but those pages break on Confluence 3.3.1 test system. So far, we have no viable workaround yet...

{code}
public void setPluginEventManager(PluginEventManager pluginEventManager)
   {
       pluginEventManager.register(this);
   }

public void handleEvent(Event event)
   {
       clearCache();
   }
{code}

Since handleEvent responds to everything that inherits from Event it'll respond to pretty much anything, since ConfluenceEvent extends Event. So for instance when someone performs a Search, this cache will get cleared.

I assume that what you want is to only clear the cache when something relevant to i18n happens, which is probably just plugin modules being enabled and disabled.

