h5. Bug Description

# When using {recently-updated-dashboard} macro using the showProfilePic=true parameter, the icons for the add and subtract are not displayed. 
# Looking at the source:
{code} 
 <div class="tabletitle fullWidth">
    <div class="tabletitleops">
                    &nbsp;                             <a class="tabletitleop" href="/pages/viewpage.action?title=esrsers&amp;spaceKey=ds&amp;maxRecentlyUpdatedPageCount=20" title="Show More"><img src="/s/1911/28/_/images/icons/add_12.png"></a>
            </div>
    Recently Updated</div>
{code} 
It looks like the macro is finding for the image add_12.png. However, there's no such image in the directory.
# In older versions, the source looks like the following:
{code}
    <div class="tabletitle fullWidth">
    <div class="tabletitleops">
                    &nbsp;                             <a class="tabletitleop" href="/pages/viewpage.action?title=esrsers&amp;spaceKey=ds&amp;maxRecentlyUpdatedPageCount=20" title="Show More"><img src="/s/1911/28/_/images/icons/add_12.gif"></a>
            </div>
    Recently Updated</div>
{code}
The image used was add_12.gif.
# The same goes for the subtract icon. In Confluence Dashboard Macros 1.15, subtract icon searched is subtract_12.png, however the one available in file system is subtract_12.gif
# This happens only when the showProfilePic=true  parameter is used

h5. Screenshots
# Using Confluence Dashboard Macros 1.13 with the following code:
{code}
{recently-updated-dashboard:dashboard} 
{recently-updated-dashboard:dashboard|showProfilePic=true} 
{code}
!ConfluenceDashboardMacros_RecentlyUpdatedDashboard113.png!

# Using Confluence Dashboard Macros 1.15 with the following code:
{code}
{recently-updated-dashboard:dashboard} 
{recently-updated-dashboard:dashboard|showProfilePic=true} 
{code}
!ConfluenceDashboardMacros_RecentlyUpdatedDashboard115.png!

h5. Workaround
Use the bundled version of Confluence Dashboard Macros. You can uninstall the current one and restart the Confluence instance to get back the bundled version.

